</emphasis>
First recorded from Lihir Group, Namatamai District, 
<collectingRegion box="[1058,1199,797,822]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fry, G. C. &amp; Brewer, D. T. &amp; Venables, W. N." box="[1247,1432,797,822]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="126 - 141" refId="ref188009" refString="Fry, G. C., Brewer, D. T. &amp; Venables, W. N. (2006) Vulnerability of deepwater demersal fishes to commercial fishing: Evidence from a study around a tropical volcanic seamount in Papua New Guinea. Fisheries Research, 81, 126 - 141." type="journal article" year="2006">
Fry 
<emphasis box="[1295,1347,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
. (2006
</bibRefCitation>
: 130). Confirmed records from an observer program on shark longline vessels in 2014 (NFA and CSIRO, unpublished data); commonly observed by dive operators; caught by artisanal fishers (W. White). A set of jaws collected from Cape Saint George in 1965 (KFRS E048) recently confirmed as this species (
<bibRefCitation author="White, W. T. &amp; Ko'ou, A." box="[1191,1432,905,930]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref198285" refString="White, W. T. &amp; Ko'ou, A. (2018) Annotated checklist of the chondrichthyans of Papua New Guinea. Zootaxa, 4411 (1), 1 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4411.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">White &amp; Ko'ou 2018</bibRefCitation>
: 31). A specimen photographed by Serge Andréfouët off the southern tip of Bauddisson Island, Kavieng District, St. KVG15, on 
<date box="[288,446,978,1002]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="2014-08-17">17 Aug. 2014</date>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
