<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,151,176]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[504,649,151,176]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5.—General distribution: Red Sea, East Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1432,151,176]" name="Seychelles" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,286,188,213]" name="Madagascar" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and Mascarenes east to Hawaiian Islands and 
<collectingCountry box="[803,894,189,212]" name="Panama" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Panama</collectingCountry>
, north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1102,1166,189,212]" name="Japan" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Japan</collectingCountry>
and Ogasawara Islands, south to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[348,454,223,248]" name="Australia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[465,638,223,248]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and Tuamotu Archipelago. Found throughout the water column, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="400.0" valueMax="800.0" valueMin="0.0">0–800 m</quantity>
depth. Marine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
